what happened.

00:51.926 --> 00:52.385
{\an8}<i>[piano trill]</i>

00:52.469 --> 00:53.344
{\an8}- Oh, yeah.

00:53.428 --> 00:55.305
{\an8}- Gotta make it

00:55.388 --> 00:55.889
{\an8}to Run of the Mill Pizza
before they close.

00:55.972 --> 00:57.724
{\an8}- Mmm, I can't wait to try

00:57.807 --> 01:00.101
{\an8}their new meatless option:
Vegetable.

01:00.185 --> 01:01.978
{\an8}- Say no more,<i> mis hermanos.</i>
- Huh?

01:02.061 --> 01:04.480
{\an8}- I'll use my ultrareliable
portaling sword

01:04.563 --> 01:06.691
{\an8}to get us there.

01:06.775 --> 01:07.776
{\an8}Hachi machi!

01:07.859 --> 01:09.444
{\an8}- No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:09.527 --> 01:12.197
{\an8}[all screaming]

01:14.240 --> 01:15.450
{\an8}- Ugh!
Huh?

01:15.533 --> 01:16.659
{\an8}[siren wails distantly]

01:16.743 --> 01:19.078
{\an8}Oy vey.

01:19.162 --> 01:21.956
I came out fine, but when they
came out, they didn't come out.

01:22.040 --> 01:23.666
My brothers are gone.

01:23.750 --> 01:26.336
{\an3}- Ah, this sounds like
a classic case

01:26.419 --> 01:28.046
of porthole jacking.

01:28.129 --> 01:28.588
{\an1}- Uh, duh.

01:28.671 --> 01:31.174
What's porthole jacking?

01:31.257 --> 01:33.343
<i>Hidden City pirates can steal</i>
<i>the contents of a portal,</i>

01:33.426 --> 01:38.681
{\an3}especially if the portal maker
is, shall we say, lame.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.058
- [chuckles]

01:40.141 --> 01:41.893
{\an1}You'll have plenty more
chances to zing me

01:41.976 --> 01:44.103
{\an1}while you help me
find my brothers.<i> Vámonos!</i>

01:47.273 --> 01:48.233
- [sighs]

01:48.316 --> 01:51.569
While I would like to help
my favorite customer,

01:51.653 --> 01:52.654
you're not him.

01:52.737 --> 01:54.030
{\an8}<i>[angelic music]</i>

01:54.113 --> 01:56.366
And I do not go
to the Hidden City.

01:56.449 --> 01:57.867
Look on the bright side:

01:57.951 --> 02:00.370
you'll get used to
the crushing loneliness.

02:00.453 --> 02:02.789
- Ugh, look, bone man.

02:02.872 --> 02:03.915
My brothers and I
buy enough pizza

02:03.998 --> 02:07.710
{\an1}to put Hueso, Jr.,
through bone college.

02:07.794 --> 02:09.878
{\an1}Have you seen
our frequent buyer card?

02:09.963 --> 02:10.547
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

02:10.630 --> 02:12.131
- [sighs]
Fine.

02:12.215 --> 02:15.385
I will show you the way
to the Hidden City,

02:15.468 --> 02:18.429
but my help ends there.

02:19.305 --> 02:21.266
- The Hidden City
is in the trash?

02:21.349 --> 02:24.519
- There are many doorways,
but this one fits you best.

02:24.602 --> 02:28.731
[compactor clunking]

02:28.815 --> 02:30.567
- Sweet, in we go.

02:30.650 --> 02:31.901
- No, no, I am not--
wha?

02:31.985 --> 02:33.236
- [screams]

02:34.779 --> 02:37.657
[both screaming]

02:37.740 --> 02:40.243
- Ugh, ugh.

02:40.326 --> 02:41.327
[groans]

02:41.411 --> 02:45.081
Whoa, who's your architect,
Frank Lloyd Gargoyle?

02:45.164 --> 02:47.584
- You fool!
You should not have brought me!

02:47.667 --> 02:49.752
{\an3}- Halt!

02:49.836 --> 02:51.087
Hidden City Police!

02:51.170 --> 02:54.757
{\an3}- Hueso? How dare you show
your skull here.

02:54.841 --> 02:56.342
We're taking you in!

02:56.426 --> 02:57.427
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
- Huh?

02:57.510 --> 02:58.469
Gah.

02:58.553 --> 03:01.180
- [grunting]

03:03.433 --> 03:04.726
- Ah!

03:04.809 --> 03:07.020
- You'll pay for this!

03:07.103 --> 03:11.983
- I, Baron Draxum,
humbly apologize!

03:12.859 --> 03:14.110
- [panting]

03:14.193 --> 03:18.072
- Señor Hueso,
are you a wanted man?

03:18.156 --> 03:19.657
- Yes!
[screams]

03:19.741 --> 03:20.283
- [chuckles]

03:20.366 --> 03:22.619
You are full of surprises.

03:22.702 --> 03:25.288
- You have no idea.

03:25.371 --> 03:26.289
- [gasps]

03:26.372 --> 03:27.999
- So long, amigo!

03:28.082 --> 03:30.376
- Huh!
- No, no, no, no, no!

03:30.460 --> 03:31.252
- [chuckles]

03:31.336 --> 03:33.004
- Do you have any idea
how much danger

03:33.087 --> 03:34.005
you have put me in?

03:34.088 --> 03:35.924
- I do now, so where we goin'?

03:36.007 --> 03:38.092
{\an1}- Where the police
dare not go.

03:38.176 --> 03:40.386
- Splinter's laundry pile?

03:45.058 --> 03:47.477
{\an1}- Ugh!
[groans]

03:47.560 --> 03:48.645
- [whistles]

03:48.728 --> 03:50.855
all: ♪ Yar har, yar har ♪

03:50.939 --> 03:52.607
♪ The baddest pirates
by far, far ♪

03:52.690 --> 03:54.984
♪ We takes your portal,
it makes us chortle ♪

03:55.068 --> 03:55.985
♪ Blah, blah, blah, blah ♪

03:56.069 --> 03:57.153
♪ We're pirates,
not lyricists ♪

03:57.236 --> 04:00.073
- Ooh, the docks.
Interesting vibe,

04:00.156 --> 04:02.533
{\an1}sort of Cape Cod
meets state prison.

04:02.617 --> 04:03.660
- Okay, here is the plan:

04:03.743 --> 04:07.622
{\an3}you stay here, and I will
find a way back to New York.

04:07.705 --> 04:08.498
- Dude, let me say this

04:08.581 --> 04:09.916
{\an1}in a language
you can understand: no.

04:09.999 --> 04:11.542
{\an1}I saved your tailbone
back there.

04:11.626 --> 04:13.795
You owe me.

04:13.878 --> 04:18.007
- Okay,<i> pepino,</i> if this is
the only way I get out of here

04:18.091 --> 04:21.260
in 206 pieces,
I will give you what you need.

04:21.344 --> 04:21.970
Come.

04:22.053 --> 04:23.888
Do you see that one over there?

04:23.972 --> 04:26.099
{\an3}That one knows everything
you need to know.

04:26.182 --> 04:28.810
Now, you go show him
who is the top dog.

04:28.893 --> 04:29.936
- Hard as nails!

04:30.019 --> 04:32.021
{\an1}All right, pipsqueak,
I'm top dog,

04:32.105 --> 04:34.857
{\an1}and you're gonna
answer my questions.

04:34.941 --> 04:36.359
- Huh?

04:36.442 --> 04:37.193
{\an1}- Huh?

04:37.276 --> 04:39.737
{\an3}- [growls]
You hasslin' my gram-gram?

04:39.821 --> 04:42.073
- He says he's top dog.

04:42.156 --> 04:43.992
- [chuckles nervously]

04:44.075 --> 04:45.660
- I'm top dog!

04:45.743 --> 04:47.537
<i>[dog barks]</i>

04:47.620 --> 04:49.288
- Ah!
- [yells]

04:49.372 --> 04:50.331
- Oh.

04:50.415 --> 04:51.207
[groans]

04:51.290 --> 04:53.209
Señor, I didn't do so good.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.169
You are not ditching me here!

04:55.253 --> 04:56.879
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

04:56.963 --> 04:58.923
Get back here,
you skinless coward!

04:59.007 --> 05:01.134
You're gonna help me
find my brothers.

05:01.801 --> 05:03.928
<i>- Estúpido.</i>

05:04.012 --> 05:06.556
[screams]

05:06.639 --> 05:08.599
- Get in here.

05:08.683 --> 05:09.809
<i>[mystical music]</i>

05:09.892 --> 05:11.769
[both screaming]

05:11.853 --> 05:14.564
You, you set me up!

05:14.647 --> 05:16.149
- I did, yes.

05:16.232 --> 05:18.568
- I ought to portal you
right back to the cops.

05:18.651 --> 05:20.528
- Hmm, with no sword?

05:20.611 --> 05:22.488
{\an3}- Uh, no.
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

05:22.572 --> 05:24.532
[screams]

05:24.615 --> 05:25.283
Portal jacked again?

05:25.366 --> 05:27.076
First my brothers,
now my sword.

05:27.160 --> 05:28.494
{\an1}What's gonna happen
the next time?

05:28.578 --> 05:32.665
{\an1}Oh, wait, there won't be a next
time because I have no sword.

05:32.749 --> 05:34.792
Oh!

05:34.876 --> 05:36.753
{\an3}- There, there.
You will be fine.

05:36.836 --> 05:37.712
{\an3}Good-bye.

05:37.795 --> 05:39.797
- I will not be fine.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.549
{\an1}There's no team
with just a faceman.

05:41.632 --> 05:43.384
I need my brainy guy
and my smashy guy

05:43.468 --> 05:44.886
and my "eats peanut butter
with his fingers" guy.

05:44.969 --> 05:49.098
I'm nothing without them.

05:49.182 --> 05:50.141
You wouldn't understand.

05:50.224 --> 05:53.853
{\an1}I guess your heart's
made of bone too.

05:53.936 --> 05:55.730
Adios, Hueso.

05:55.813 --> 05:57.940
{\an3}- [sighs]

05:58.024 --> 05:59.233
<i>Pepino,</i> wait.

05:59.317 --> 06:02.779
{\an3}I do know what it is
to lose someone.

06:02.862 --> 06:04.614
I will help you.

06:04.697 --> 06:09.243
{\an3}The theft of your sword might
be a blessing in disguise.

06:09.327 --> 06:11.370
{\an1}This shop is known
for selling stolen weapons.

06:11.454 --> 06:13.664
The portal thieves may come
here to unload your sword.

06:13.748 --> 06:16.250
- There they are!

06:16.334 --> 06:18.044
Bonehead, you're a genius.

06:18.127 --> 06:20.296
Hot soup!

06:20.379 --> 06:21.881
Yah!

06:22.715 --> 06:25.093
- [grunting]

06:25.176 --> 06:27.512
[chuckles]

06:27.595 --> 06:29.514
<i>Olé!</i>

06:29.597 --> 06:31.349
{\an3}- [laughs]
Oh!

06:31.432 --> 06:33.726
{\an3}Huh?

06:33.810 --> 06:35.394
- The "Queen Alexis."

06:35.478 --> 06:37.105
{\an3}- That must be the ship
where they've got my bros.

06:37.188 --> 06:40.525
{\an3}Raph, Mikey,
I guess maybe Donnie,

06:40.608 --> 06:41.442
I'm coming for ya!

06:41.526 --> 06:43.820
{\an9}- We'll need disguises
to get onboard.

06:44.570 --> 06:48.866
{\an3}You went with
two eye patches, eh?

06:48.950 --> 06:49.617
- I think I know
what I'm doin'.

06:49.700 --> 06:50.868
{\an1}Ugh!

06:50.952 --> 06:52.537
So where's the ship?

06:52.620 --> 06:54.539
{\an1}- There!

06:54.622 --> 06:57.625
- Sky pirates,
you are goin' down!

06:57.708 --> 06:58.334
[sword zinging]

06:58.417 --> 07:01.712
{\an1}- Wait, we need
to formulate a...

07:01.796 --> 07:02.839
{\an3}[screams]

07:02.922 --> 07:05.341
[both screaming]

07:09.470 --> 07:10.179
Plan.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.765
{\an1}- Don't worry,
my plan is to wing it.

07:12.849 --> 07:13.891
{\an3}- Oy vey.

07:13.975 --> 07:16.853
- Yar, who be ye?

07:16.936 --> 07:19.313
- Who be we?

07:19.397 --> 07:20.815
We be yar ship's entertainment.

07:20.898 --> 07:22.483
I'm Captain Bluemask,

07:22.567 --> 07:26.863
{\an1}and this is my hilarious
sidekick, Jolly Roger.

07:26.946 --> 07:29.866
{\an1}Boy, Rog,
you sure have lost weight.

07:29.949 --> 07:31.701
- Please, do not do this.

07:31.784 --> 07:35.705
{\an1}- Okay, looks like somebody's
lost his funny bone.

07:35.788 --> 07:36.706
<i>[accordion flourish]</i>

07:36.789 --> 07:37.665
<i>[crickets chirp]</i>

07:37.748 --> 07:42.003
- That joke is so lame,
it requires a peg leg.

07:42.086 --> 07:43.796
[laughter]

07:43.880 --> 07:45.506
{\an3}- I get it!

07:45.590 --> 07:46.549
- That was good.
That was good.

07:46.632 --> 07:48.384
But, remember,
you're the straight man.

07:48.467 --> 07:50.720
{\an1}Boy, this Hidden City weather,
am I right?

07:50.803 --> 07:54.056
Speaking of which, what's
the deal with portal jacking?

07:54.140 --> 07:56.267
Anybody done
any of that lately?

07:56.350 --> 07:57.268
- That hits too close to home!

07:57.351 --> 07:59.687
- I'm starting to think
these two

07:59.770 --> 08:01.856
are not a polished
ventriloquist act.

08:01.939 --> 08:04.358
- Hueso.
- Huh?

08:08.362 --> 08:11.282
- Piel!
- It is Capitán Piel to you.

08:11.365 --> 08:15.578
{\an8}<i>[triumphant musical flourish]</i>

08:15.661 --> 08:16.329
{\an8}<i>- Ew.</i>

08:16.412 --> 08:17.872
- Be careful, my crew.

08:17.955 --> 08:19.999
{\an3}It is the most wanted pirate
in the Hidden City.

08:20.082 --> 08:23.377
- Yar, right.
[laughter]

08:23.461 --> 08:25.046
- Wait a sec,
you were a pirate?

08:25.129 --> 08:25.922
Dude, you're killin' it today!

08:26.005 --> 08:28.257
- I was never a pirate.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.718
{\an1}He tricked me into
going on one mission,

08:30.801 --> 08:33.804
{\an1}and I'm forever branded
a criminal in the Hidden City.

08:33.888 --> 08:35.597
- You were such a coward,

08:35.681 --> 08:38.226
{\an3}you ran away
from a basic plundering.

08:38.308 --> 08:40.937
{\an3}Ha, you should have heard
his bones rattle.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.104
- I was but a child!

08:42.188 --> 08:44.774
{\an1}But I fear you no more,
<i>hermano.</i>

08:44.857 --> 08:47.485
- [chuckles]

08:47.568 --> 08:51.030
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
<i>hermano?</i>

08:51.113 --> 08:52.073
You guys are--

08:52.156 --> 08:54.075
- Yes, we are brothers.

08:54.158 --> 08:55.618
One last chance, Piel.

08:55.701 --> 08:57.745
{\an1}Leave this life,
and we can be brothers again.

08:57.828 --> 09:00.915
- You know the old saying:
skin and bones do not mix.

09:00.998 --> 09:05.253
{\an3}[laughing]

09:05.336 --> 09:06.837
- [screams]

09:06.921 --> 09:08.881
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

09:08.965 --> 09:13.678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:13.761 --> 09:15.096
- Avast, ye!

09:15.179 --> 09:17.306
[laughing]

09:17.390 --> 09:19.433
- [screams]

09:20.434 --> 09:22.270
{\an3}- Okay, maybe you're better off
without your brother,

09:22.353 --> 09:24.689
{\an3}but I'm still
gonna get mine.

09:24.772 --> 09:25.064
- [laughs]

09:25.147 --> 09:27.775
- [grunting]

09:30.611 --> 09:32.363
{\an1}Ah!

09:32.446 --> 09:34.740
{\an3}- Looks like you're done,
matey.

09:34.824 --> 09:39.620
- Oh? Not if I portal you
to the Hidden City Police.

09:39.704 --> 09:40.663
Hachi machi!

09:40.746 --> 09:43.499
{\an3}<i>- Pepino,</i>
this has never worked.

09:43.582 --> 09:45.001
- Ah!

09:48.254 --> 09:51.173
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

09:51.257 --> 09:53.301
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:53.384 --> 09:54.218
[all scream]

09:54.302 --> 09:57.221
- Whoa, where'd you guys
come from?

09:57.305 --> 09:59.515
I mean, hey, check it out.

09:59.598 --> 10:01.851
I freed you
from your pirate prison.

10:01.934 --> 10:03.227
You're welcome.

10:03.311 --> 10:04.437
- Pirate prison?

10:04.520 --> 10:06.355
{\an3}- You portaled us
to Tahiti.

10:06.439 --> 10:09.483
{\an1}- The sewers there
are fabulous.

10:09.817 --> 10:11.110
- Whoo-ha!

10:11.193 --> 10:12.737
Come on, come on, come on,
help us fight these guys.

10:12.820 --> 10:15.281
{\an1}- No, I want a refill
on my coconut.

10:15.364 --> 10:16.782
- Take us back to Tahiti.

10:16.866 --> 10:18.034
- More Tahiti!

10:18.117 --> 10:20.161
{\an9}- It would get us
out of this.

10:20.244 --> 10:23.080
{\an8}Okay, Tahiti,
here we come!

10:23.164 --> 10:26.125
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

10:26.208 --> 10:27.293
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:27.376 --> 10:28.753
{\an3}- Ah, no.

10:28.836 --> 10:30.629
- [screams]

10:34.300 --> 10:36.886
- Oh, is this Tahiti?

10:36.969 --> 10:38.721
Well, then allow me
to make a sand angel

10:38.804 --> 10:40.890
in this lovely
soft wooden sand. Ouch.

10:40.973 --> 10:43.434
{\an1}- Okay, not what I meant to do,
but I got rid of the pirates.

10:43.517 --> 10:46.145
[horn blaring]
- You sure did!

10:46.228 --> 10:47.730
{\an1}- Huh?

10:47.813 --> 10:50.232
- Uh, we were, uh, bravely
surveilling the situation

10:50.316 --> 10:52.860
and we saw what happened.

10:52.943 --> 10:54.528
You're a hero, Hueso.

10:54.612 --> 10:57.073
- Then I am off
the most wanted list?

10:57.156 --> 10:58.532
- Well, ya are now.

10:58.616 --> 11:00.201
- Ah, gracias,<i> pepino.</i>

11:00.284 --> 11:02.703
- No problem, bone man.

11:02.787 --> 11:05.581
- What do you suppose
has become of my brother?

11:05.664 --> 11:09.502
- Oh, I guarantee I sent him
to the worst place possible.

11:09.585 --> 11:13.839
- And what is the deal
with plundering, eh?

11:13.923 --> 11:15.549
[laughter]

11:17.176 --> 11:18.260
<i>all: ♪ Birthday girl,</i>
<i>it's your birthday ♪</i>

11:18.344 --> 11:19.095
<i>♪ Birthday girl,</i>
<i>it's your birthday ♪</i>

11:19.178 --> 11:21.722
{\an1}- I don't know why
you are even bothering.

11:21.806 --> 11:25.684
{\an1}I told you guys my birthdays
are always a disaster.

11:25.768 --> 11:26.102
It's cursed.

11:26.185 --> 11:28.270
- Curse, smursh.

11:28.354 --> 11:30.231
We are gonna birthday so hard,

11:30.314 --> 11:32.066
you're gonna need
a permission slip.

11:32.149 --> 11:33.067
[loud crash]

11:33.150 --> 11:34.610
[all groan]

11:34.693 --> 11:35.903
- What was that?

11:35.986 --> 11:36.987
[engine hissing]

11:37.071 --> 11:38.489
{\an3}- Ah!

11:38.572 --> 11:40.324
{\an8}- Oh, I guess the cannon works.

11:40.408 --> 11:40.950
{\an8}Power level, good.

11:41.033 --> 11:43.327
{\an8}Aim, needs work.

11:43.411 --> 11:45.246
{\an7}- Are you sure
it's safe for my hair

11:45.329 --> 11:48.082
{\an7}to shoot me
out of this thing?

11:48.165 --> 11:49.750
{\an8}- Of course.

11:49.834 --> 11:52.336
{\an8}Magician's assistants have been
shot out of cannons for years.

11:52.420 --> 11:54.130
{\an8}But if you're concerned,

11:54.213 --> 11:56.590
{\an9}we could go back
to sawing you in ten.

11:56.674 --> 12:01.971
{\an8}- Newsflash: you actually
saw me into tiny pieces.

12:02.054 --> 12:03.639
{\an8}It's incredibly painful.

12:03.722 --> 12:05.057
{\an9}- Well, you don't
think it's painful,

12:05.141 --> 12:06.559
{\an9}me, cutting
my roomie up?

12:06.642 --> 12:08.686
{\an8}I'm a mutant,
not a monster.

12:08.769 --> 12:09.895
[loud thumping]

12:09.979 --> 12:11.230
They found us.

12:11.313 --> 12:13.858
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:13.941 --> 12:15.651
- Play it cool.

12:15.734 --> 12:17.194
- Hard to do without
an air conditioner.

12:17.278 --> 12:19.613
<i>[rim shot]</i>

12:19.697 --> 12:20.322
- Nailed it.

12:20.406 --> 12:21.866
- Ah, it was a great setup.

12:23.534 --> 12:25.119
<i>- Okay, give it to me</i>
<i>straight.</i>

12:25.202 --> 12:27.455
<i>How bad is the damage?</i>

12:27.538 --> 12:29.081
{\an3}- Oh, it's, uh,
not that bad.

12:29.165 --> 12:31.375
- Oh, it's real bad,

12:31.459 --> 12:34.587
{\an1}real, real, real, real, real,
real, real, real, real bad.

12:34.670 --> 12:37.173
- See, I told you
my birthday was cursed.

12:37.256 --> 12:38.799
- Come on, relax.

12:38.883 --> 12:41.510
{\an3}This is just a mini bump
in the road, a hiccup.

12:41.594 --> 12:44.305
{\an3}There's no way
this night gets worse.

12:44.388 --> 12:45.806
[explosion]

12:45.890 --> 12:48.142
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:48.225 --> 12:50.644
- Ugh!

12:50.728 --> 12:51.687
- Ah!

12:51.770 --> 12:52.188
- What was that?

12:52.271 --> 12:54.356
- [groans]

12:54.440 --> 12:57.568
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

12:57.651 --> 13:00.946
- Your gauntlet
will be mine, worm man.

13:02.948 --> 13:06.827
- Breaking news:
the gauntlet stays with me!

13:06.911 --> 13:09.788
[lasers zapping]

13:10.956 --> 13:11.332
- Enough of this.

13:11.415 --> 13:13.417
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:13.501 --> 13:16.003
- Oh, ah, ooh, ah, oh!

13:16.086 --> 13:17.046
Huh?

13:17.129 --> 13:20.174
- Alakaboom!

13:20.257 --> 13:22.218
<i>[tinkling music]</i>

13:22.301 --> 13:24.929
{\an1}- Take that,
you horn-headed freak!

13:26.514 --> 13:30.726
- Oh, my turtles,
how very not nice to see you.

13:34.480 --> 13:36.565
- April's birthday
really is cursed.

13:36.649 --> 13:39.151
{\an3}- We cannot
let her see this.

13:39.235 --> 13:40.027
- Yeah, we gotta
get out of here.

13:40.110 --> 13:41.695
- [grunts]

13:41.779 --> 13:44.823
- Real quick, we just
need to take care

13:44.907 --> 13:47.618
of this tiny, no-big-deal,
non-life-threatening situation.

13:47.701 --> 13:50.496
Then it's on
to April birthday fun.

13:50.579 --> 13:53.207
- Prepare to fire
some cool weapons!

13:53.290 --> 13:54.750
- Which ones?

13:54.833 --> 13:56.544
- All of them.

13:57.670 --> 14:01.423
{\an3}- Okay, who is that,
and how'd he get in here?

14:01.507 --> 14:02.424
{\an1}- [gasps]
Hold the phone!

14:02.508 --> 14:04.552
You're Warren Stone.

14:04.635 --> 14:06.428
{\an3}I'd recognize
that hair anywhere!

14:06.512 --> 14:08.305
- Why, yes, I am.

14:08.389 --> 14:10.140
Are you a Stonehead?

14:10.224 --> 14:12.560
That's what I call my fans.

14:12.643 --> 14:15.104
- Member since ♪ 2010 ♪

14:15.187 --> 14:16.480
- Excellent.

14:16.564 --> 14:19.900
{\an1}Now by the power vested in me
by my own fan club,

14:19.984 --> 14:24.154
{\an1}I'm deputizing you
to get my hippo roomie back.

14:25.739 --> 14:29.493
- Where's my roommate/friend/
magical assistant?

14:29.577 --> 14:31.287
{\an1}- Surprise!
We don't have him.

14:31.370 --> 14:32.288
Uh, they have him.

14:32.371 --> 14:34.540
Double surprise.

14:34.623 --> 14:35.958
- Get off my console!

14:36.041 --> 14:38.002
- I'll save you, Warren!

14:38.085 --> 14:40.838
Ah!

14:42.715 --> 14:43.966
- No!

14:44.049 --> 14:46.260
Give him back!

14:46.343 --> 14:47.303
{\an1}- Oh, no.

14:47.386 --> 14:49.763
[explosion]

14:49.847 --> 14:49.972
- Wha?

14:52.975 --> 14:54.685
- Warren!

14:54.768 --> 14:57.354
- Hypno!

14:57.438 --> 14:59.982
- Warren!

15:00.065 --> 15:02.526
{\an1}- Hypno!

15:02.943 --> 15:06.614
[all screaming]

15:07.406 --> 15:11.118
<i>[ominous music]</i>

15:13.912 --> 15:14.955
- Oh.

15:15.039 --> 15:18.208
{\an3}- What does this thing do,
and why does Draxum want it?

15:18.292 --> 15:19.376
{\an3}Hmm? Hmm?

15:19.460 --> 15:21.503
- I don't know,
but it's amazing.

15:21.587 --> 15:23.005
I call her Charlotte.

15:23.088 --> 15:25.841
She's like a toupee
but for your fist.

15:25.924 --> 15:28.510
- The gauntlet is part
of the dark armor.

15:28.594 --> 15:29.553
We cannot let Draxum have it.

15:29.637 --> 15:32.348
So now to do
some light removing

15:32.431 --> 15:33.515
of a thing
attached to another thing.

15:33.599 --> 15:36.352
{\an3}- What the?
Donnie!

15:36.435 --> 15:38.354
{\an1}- It's fine.
He regenerates, remember?

15:38.437 --> 15:40.856
{\an3}- Uh, no.

15:40.939 --> 15:42.691
[flames roaring,
metal clanking]

15:42.775 --> 15:44.109
{\an1}- Stop!
This is a sign.

15:44.193 --> 15:46.820
{\an1}Maybe this is finally the year
my birthday is awesome.

15:46.904 --> 15:49.698
{\an3}- Because we've got a worm man
tied to a pole?

15:49.782 --> 15:52.493
{\an3}You need to raise
your standards.

15:52.576 --> 15:53.369
- This is my birthday,

15:53.452 --> 15:55.037
{\an1}and Warren Stone
is the GOAT of news anchors.

15:55.120 --> 15:58.415
{\an1}We've gotta help him get his
friend/roomie/it's complicated

15:58.499 --> 16:00.584
back from Baron Draxum.

16:00.668 --> 16:01.251
It's my birthday wish.

16:01.335 --> 16:03.337
[all groan]

16:03.420 --> 16:05.005
{\an3}- You're invoking
B-day rights on him?

16:05.089 --> 16:07.841
{\an1}- He might be a villain,
but so is Baron Sheep Man,

16:07.925 --> 16:11.220
{\an1}and the enemy of your enemy
is a--monster!

16:11.303 --> 16:12.221
- [squeals]

16:12.304 --> 16:13.889
[all scream]

16:13.972 --> 16:16.100
{\an3}- [squeals]

16:18.519 --> 16:19.228
{\an3}- Is that a note
from Draxum?

16:19.311 --> 16:21.730
- What, he couldn't
send an email?

16:21.814 --> 16:24.566
<i>- "Give us the gauntlet</i>
<i>or your kiwi friend</i>

16:24.650 --> 16:26.068
<i>"becomes a smoothie.</i>

16:26.151 --> 16:29.613
<i>"Let's not be tacky and avoid</i>
<i>a violent exchang...ie.</i>

16:29.697 --> 16:32.908
{\an8}<i>Love, Huginn and Muninn."</i>

16:32.991 --> 16:34.952
{\an3}- You guys,
we gotta help 'em.

16:35.035 --> 16:35.869
- Hard pass.

16:35.953 --> 16:38.205
- [whimpering]
<i>[soft music]</i>

16:38.288 --> 16:42.751
- I know I'm a famous worm
villain, but I need your help.

16:42.835 --> 16:45.754
<i>When news fame left,</i>
<i>so did everyone I knew.</i>

16:45.838 --> 16:47.923
<i>I was alone.</i>
<i>I had nothing,</i>

16:48.006 --> 16:51.510
<i>until I met a magician</i>
<i>turned hippo,</i>

16:51.593 --> 16:54.012
<i>and my life changed.</i>

16:54.096 --> 16:57.057
<i>For my birthday,</i>
<i>he baked me a tiny cake</i>

16:57.141 --> 16:59.101
<i>and then magically</i>
<i>jumped out of it.</i>

16:59.184 --> 17:03.397
<i>He almost crushed me</i>
<i>when he slipped on frosting.</i>

17:03.480 --> 17:04.940
He's my brother.
He's my--

17:05.022 --> 17:07.651
- Fine. All right.
Just please stop.

17:07.734 --> 17:11.155
We'll get your roomie back.

17:11.238 --> 17:14.450
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:14.532 --> 17:16.285
- [muffled groan]

17:16.367 --> 17:19.413
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:19.496 --> 17:23.459
- Tonight's top story: I'm here
to make your trade, Draxum.

17:23.541 --> 17:25.627
- Good.

17:25.711 --> 17:27.296
Now hand over
the gauntlet.

17:27.378 --> 17:28.297
- [muffled]
It's a trap!

17:28.380 --> 17:31.091
- I love you too.

17:31.175 --> 17:35.679
We could do that, or I could
make you an even sweeter offer.

17:35.763 --> 17:36.680
- Ooh, like what?

17:36.764 --> 17:38.182
- A lifetime supply of gum?

17:38.265 --> 17:39.433
- No.

17:39.516 --> 17:41.810
{\an8}- How about
your mutant loser turtles?

17:41.894 --> 17:42.644
I brought them right here.

17:42.728 --> 17:44.438
{\an3}- Wait, did he
just give us up?

17:44.521 --> 17:46.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:46.523 --> 17:49.026
[all groan]

17:49.109 --> 17:50.986
- Betrayal!

17:51.069 --> 17:53.155
I feel like we should
have seen that coming.

17:53.238 --> 17:55.908
- How could you do this?
And on my birthday.

17:55.991 --> 17:58.952
I was the vice president
of the Stoneheads.

17:59.036 --> 17:59.703
- [exhales]

17:59.787 --> 18:00.746
And he thanks you
for your service.

18:00.829 --> 18:03.665
- [chuckling]
Whoa.

18:03.749 --> 18:06.418
You drive a hard bargain.

18:06.502 --> 18:10.172
But it's a deal.

18:10.255 --> 18:12.174
Free him.
- Ah!

18:12.257 --> 18:13.801
{\an1}[groans]

18:13.884 --> 18:15.594
- Tonight's headline:

18:15.677 --> 18:18.013
{\an3}best friends
reunited and it feels--

18:18.096 --> 18:19.097
- I'm so sorry.

18:19.181 --> 18:22.017
It was the only way
he'd let you live.

18:22.100 --> 18:23.393
- Huh?

18:23.477 --> 18:26.313
- Oh, mezmeroo!

18:26.396 --> 18:31.443
Oh, give them the gauntlet,
my golden voiced amigo.

18:32.820 --> 18:35.531
- Oh, man, a double betrayal.

18:35.614 --> 18:37.491
Did not see that coming.

18:37.574 --> 18:39.535
- You get the gauntlet
and the turtles

18:39.618 --> 18:41.537
and Warren lives.

18:41.620 --> 18:43.247
That was our deal, right?

18:44.206 --> 18:44.540
{\an1}- Yeah, no.
I lied.

18:44.623 --> 18:46.500
- Huh?
Ah!

18:46.583 --> 18:48.752
- Triple betrayal!

18:48.836 --> 18:51.964
{\an3}Everybody's
on fire tonight.

18:53.048 --> 18:55.717
{\an3}- But you said--
you promised.

18:55.801 --> 18:56.969
- Only a true genius
could choreograph

18:57.052 --> 18:59.847
this many betrayals
and double-crosses.

18:59.930 --> 19:02.516
{\an1}- I mean, it was
a total team effort.

19:02.599 --> 19:03.809
- I am blushing.

19:03.892 --> 19:05.060
- I was talking about me,
you idiots.

19:05.144 --> 19:07.062
Now, time to do
some light removing

19:07.145 --> 19:09.565
of one thing
attached to another thing.

19:09.648 --> 19:12.192
- [grunts]

19:12.276 --> 19:13.610
[rings zinging]

19:13.694 --> 19:15.487
{\an1}- Classic April O'Neil
birthday:

19:15.571 --> 19:17.531
{\an1}trapped in a cage,
betrayed by my idol,

19:17.614 --> 19:18.740
and facing certain doom.

19:18.824 --> 19:20.868
- Look on the bright side:
we're trapped in a cage

19:20.951 --> 19:22.953
having been betrayed
by your idol

19:23.036 --> 19:25.539
facing certain doom
together.

19:25.622 --> 19:27.833
<i>[crickets chirp]</i>

19:27.916 --> 19:29.710
Hey, I'm tryin' my best here.

19:29.793 --> 19:30.335
- Huh?
- Hmm?

19:31.503 --> 19:34.423
- Ta-da!

19:34.506 --> 19:35.841
Wait, almost there.

19:35.924 --> 19:37.593
A little higher.
To the right. Hold on.

19:37.676 --> 19:40.262
And, yep, you're there.

19:40.345 --> 19:41.471
Allow me to help.

19:41.555 --> 19:42.472
- Okay, cowboy,

19:42.556 --> 19:45.350
I don't know what kind
of double triple betrayal

19:45.434 --> 19:47.895
you've got planned,
but we're not interested.

19:47.978 --> 19:49.730
{\an3}- I've got nothing
up my sleeve.

19:49.813 --> 19:50.772
{\an3}I promise.

19:50.856 --> 19:52.858
- Ah!
- Oh!

19:54.067 --> 19:56.069
- Please, you must save Warren.

19:56.153 --> 19:58.113
Look, I--I'm a terrible roomie.

19:58.196 --> 19:59.907
I--I--I cheat
on the chore chart.

19:59.990 --> 20:02.743
He pretends not to notice,
but he does. I know he does.

20:02.826 --> 20:05.996
<i>[poignant music]</i>

20:06.079 --> 20:07.789
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:07.873 --> 20:10.208
{\an1}- I just can't quit you,
Warren Stone.

20:10.292 --> 20:13.670
- To be clear,
we're doing this for April

20:13.754 --> 20:15.505
because it's her birthday.

20:15.589 --> 20:16.590
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:16.673 --> 20:19.468
[saw whirring]

20:19.551 --> 20:23.722
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:23.805 --> 20:25.682
- [groans]

20:25.766 --> 20:27.309
- Step away from my roomie.

20:27.392 --> 20:30.062
{\an3}- I've got him! I've got him!
Let's go!

20:30.145 --> 20:31.396
Ah!

20:31.480 --> 20:33.941
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:34.024 --> 20:35.734
- Little help here.

20:35.817 --> 20:38.153
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:38.236 --> 20:40.489
[all grunting]

20:40.572 --> 20:41.740
- Huh?
Ah!

20:41.823 --> 20:43.825
{\an3}- We can't stretch him
any further!

20:43.909 --> 20:47.120
- [whispers]
April O'Neil.

20:47.204 --> 20:47.537
{\an3}- Ah!

20:47.621 --> 20:48.664
[all scream]

20:48.747 --> 20:51.416
- Oh.
Huh?

20:51.500 --> 20:53.043
<i>[whimsical musical flourish]</i>

20:53.126 --> 20:55.003
{\an1}Mmm.

20:55.087 --> 20:58.548
- Finally another piece
of the dark armor.

20:58.632 --> 20:59.508
Ew, gross.

20:59.591 --> 21:03.428
- New victory dance.
- With extra butt action.

21:04.554 --> 21:06.682
- Whew.

21:06.765 --> 21:07.683
{\an3}- How'd you know
about our old trick?

21:07.766 --> 21:09.518
- What old trick?

21:09.601 --> 21:13.230
- [screams]

21:13.313 --> 21:14.356
[loud pop]

21:14.439 --> 21:16.358
I'm fine.

21:16.441 --> 21:18.527
Charlotte, my power!

21:18.610 --> 21:21.321
You've made a grave mistake.

21:21.405 --> 21:23.573
You are on my list.

21:23.657 --> 21:24.992
- It was you or the gauntlet.

21:25.075 --> 21:27.786
{\an1}And to some, well,
you're kind of a big deal.

21:27.869 --> 21:30.706
- I will haunt your dreams.

21:30.789 --> 21:32.290
<i>[gentle music]</i>

21:32.374 --> 21:33.875
- That's my Warren.

21:33.959 --> 21:35.794
Oh, it's good to have you back,

21:35.877 --> 21:38.588
{\an1}roomie/magical assistant/
friend.

21:38.672 --> 21:40.382
{\an1}[smooches]

21:40.465 --> 21:43.385
{\an1}Doves!

21:43.468 --> 21:47.639
{\an1}Let's go make fun of
game show contestants on TV.

21:47.723 --> 21:50.308
{\an3}- April,
so about your birthday.

21:50.392 --> 21:51.184
{\an3}[chuckles]

21:51.268 --> 21:52.185
We're really sorry
we weren't the ones

21:52.269 --> 21:53.770
{\an3}to break the curse
and, uh--

21:53.854 --> 21:54.438
- Happy birthday.

21:56.565 --> 21:57.983
- Uh...

21:58.066 --> 22:00.819
Best birthday ever!
